resources.string:
Use this screen to rate audio recordings that are part of a rating session.\n\n;

The first time you start the application, you will be prompted to create a new rating session.
Select the directory containing the audio recordings to be rated using the selection screen.\n\n;

If it is desirable to distinguish groups of individual recordings (e.g. healthy/sick), we recommend
placing recordings from the respective groups into individual folders and selecting the parent directory.
The application will then automatically split and mark the recordings for optional post-processing.\n\n;

The application supports these audio formats: AAC (.m4a, .aac), FLAC (.flac), MP3 (.mp3), Opus (.ogg), PCM / WAVE (.wav) and Vorbis (.ogg, .m4a).\n\n;

Use the player buttons to navigate the session recordings, play them or seek in them.
The number of plays of each recording is not limited.\n\n;

After listening, each recording can be rated using a continuous scale at the bottom of the screen.
When all recordings have been rated, a double checkmark icon will be displayed.\n\n;

Sessions are stored in the app\'s memory and saved automatically each time you leave the rating screen.\n\n;
The results can be saved either manually using the drop-down menu in the upper right corner, or, in case all recordings have been rated,
they will be saved automatically when you leave the activity.\n\n;

The results are stored in a specific application directory in the device memory and can be shared
from the "Saved Ratings" section, which can be accessed via the drop-down menu.

You can view and share your saved session results in this activity.\n\n;

Each session in the list can be clicked to display a screen containing detailed information
about the selected session. Sessions are sorted chronologically with the most recent one on top.\n\n;

A long touch on a session in the list can delete the session.\n\n;

All session results can be shared using the button at the bottom of the screen, either as a plain text file
(.txt, formatted for additional processing in programs such as Matlab, etc.) or
a Microsoft® Excel® file (.xlsx).\n\n;

Session results are stored in an application folder in the device\'s internal memory. The number
of backup session result files for the active session can be changed in the app\'s settings.

This screen displays a detailed preview of the selected session, including a list of all
individual recordings, their ratings, and a button to share the session results.\n\n;

The session information in the header can be copied to the clipboard by touching on it.\n\n;

Touching the column headers can sort the items in the recordings list using the respective column\'s values.\n\n;

Long touch on an item in the recordings list copies the recording\'s information to the clipboard.\n\n;

The displayed session can be shared using the button at the bottom of the screen.
Session can be shared either as a plain text file (.txt, formatted for additional
processing in programs such as Matlab, etc.) or as a Microsoft® Excel® file (.xlsx).

This screen displays a detailed preview of the current session, including a list of all
individual recordings, their ratings, and a button to share the session results.\n\n;

The session information in the header can be copied to the clipboard by touching on it.\n\n;

Touching the column headers can sort the items in the recordings list using the respective column\'s values.\n\n;

Long touch on an item in the recordings list copies the recording\'s information to the clipboard.\n\n;

The current session can be shared using the button at the bottom of the screen.
Session can be shared either as a plain text file (.txt, formatted for additional
processing in programs such as Matlab, etc.) or as a Microsoft® Excel® file (.xlsx).

From this screen, you can check the audio files and groups you want to use in the newly created session.\n\n;

The header shows the number of individual directories in which usable audio files were found.\n\n;

The directory list shows the name of the directory found, the number of usable audio files within,
and a field that can be used to change the group name that will be assigned to all files from that directory.
The default group name is the name of the containing directory.\n\n;

If a directory in which there are no usable files (including subfolders) has been selected,
an error message will be displayed.\n\n;

If only a directory directly containing usable audio files (no subfolders) has been selected,
it will be used and only one group will be created.\n\n;

Use the check box on the right to select whether the directory/group will be used in the session you are creating.

Here you can change the application settings.\n\n;

When changing the number of session\'s result backup files, the excess above this limit will be
deleted only for the current session upon it\'s results saving.\n\n;

You can send feedback (bugs, comments, ideas for improvement) by email using the provided option.
